// Status Manager
// Manages global agent status (working/waiting/idle) and broadcasts changes to WebSocket clients and listeners.

A single StatusManager instance (statusManager) is exported as a module-level singleton.
The WebSocket handler is injected after construction via setWebSocketHandler.

FUNCTION setWebSocketHandler(wsHandler) -> void
  Store the WebSocket handler reference for status broadcasting.

---

FUNCTION updateStatus(status, message) -> void
  CALLS: notifyListeners (status-manager)
  Update the internal status and lastActivity timestamp.
  IF a WebSocket handler is set, broadcast the new status to all connected clients.
  Notify all subscribed listeners.

---

FUNCTION getStatus() -> StatusResponse
  Return the current status, message, and lastActivity as an ISO string.

---

FUNCTION subscribe(listener) -> unsubscribe function
  Add a listener callback to the listener list.
  Return a function that removes the listener when called.

---

FUNCTION notifyListeners() -> void
  Private. Call each registered listener with the current status.
  Errors thrown by individual listeners are caught and logged but do not stop other listeners.
